Even if you plan to arrive later, you would still need to sign the contract (via e-sign) and complete the payment as required before the official move-in date.

As for the move-out date, most properties have fixed end dates, typically around early September. Extensions may not be possible, but if they are, it would depend entirely on the property‚Äôs policy. If allowed, you may be able to pay for the additional duration.

The payment schedule, including installment amounts and due dates, will be provided directly by the property and will be clearly mentioned in your contract at the time of booking.
